benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles - Retrieve a bundle by external key

covered: GET Valid Request: Happy path retrieval by externalKey (TC01) returns 200 with a single Bundle object and JSON content-type.
Audit parameter handling: TC03-TC05 verify FULL, MINIMAL, NONE audit details are returned accordingly.
IncludedDeleted handling: TC02 confirms deleted bundles are returned when includedDeleted=true; TC06 ensures deleted bundles are not returned when includedDeleted=false.
Query Parameter validation: Tests cover missing externalKey (TC07), invalid values (TC09, TC10), and extra unsupported parameters (TC15).
Non-existent vs empty dataset: TC08 (404 for non-existent) and TC16 (404 when no bundles in system) cover empty data scenarios.
Authorization: 401 Unauthorized (TC11) and 403 Forbidden (TC12) are validated.
Error/availability handling: 503 Service Unavailable in TC13 (dependency failure) and TC28 (service downtime).
Resilience: Recovery from transient failures (TC21) and backward compatibility (TC22) and non-ASCII keys (TC23) are covered.
Boundary and security tests: Long/short externalKey (TC24, TC25), unexpected input (TC26), SQLi (TC19) and XSS (TC20).
Data volume and concurrency: Duplicate-key scenarios (TC14), very large dataset (TC27), and concurrent requests (TC18) are tested.
Performance and schema: Response time check (TC17) and verification of required Bundle fields (TC30) and content-type (TC01).
gaps: Pagination: No tests covering pagination semantics or page size handling for large result sets.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses under burst load.
Caching: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional GET behavior (304).
recommendations: Add pagination tests if endpoint supports pagination, including page/limit behavior and response structure for multi-page results.
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper throttling and 429 responses under high load.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and 304 Not Modified responses, and not exposing sensitive error data.
Expand boundary and error message checks to verify exact payloads across error scenarios and ensure consistency.
